31
00:01:21,329 --> 00:01:25,025
Oh yeah? 'cause I don't see how that works, having two fathers.

32
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:39,516
Nathan woods and I got married when I was 21 years old.

33
00:01:40,757 --> 00:01:41,246
He was...

34
00:01:41,246 --> 00:01:43,777
a narcotics detective.
He told me already.

35
00:01:43,828 --> 00:01:46,266
No, Wallace, that's how he started out.

36
00:01:46,349 --> 00:01:50,691
But then he went undercover on some case that he said would make his career.

37
00:01:50,979 --> 00:01:54,121
And soon, he got so deep into it, he had me fooled,

38
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:57,488
unless coming home high was a part of the job,

39
00:01:57,612 --> 00:02:01,983
unless stashing heroin and guns under my bed was all in the line of duty.

40
00:02:10,001 --> 00:02:12,665
I hate that you had to find out like this.

41
00:02:13,588 --> 00:02:19,039
But if you are asking me who is your real father, that's Hank Fennel.

42
00:02:25,238 --> 00:02:26,561
What are you doing?

43
00:02:26,612 --> 00:02:29,604
I wanted to show you your birth certificate, but...

44
00:02:32,801 --> 00:02:34,249
I know wre it went.

45
00:02:40,871 --> 00:02:41,833
You know...

46
00:02:42,566 --> 00:02:45,398
that the day hank Fennel asked me to marry him

47
00:02:45,815 --> 00:02:50,425
was the day that he signed his name on that piece of paper, calling you his son.

48
00:02:50,769 --> 00:02:53,912
And that is who your father was.

49
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:57,104
And that's who he still is.

50
00:03:18,544 --> 00:03:19,598
Can I guess?

51
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:23,277
You got a sweet love hangover, and you don't need no cure.

52
00:03:23,460 --> 00:03:25,588
