165
00:09:16,909 --> 00:09:23,185
$100 for lip enhancer at estée lauder, $1,200 for a leather jacket at nordstrom,

166
00:09:23,468 --> 00:09:26,964
$500 on vanilla-scented candles at tricky wicks?

167
00:09:27,288 --> 00:09:30,246
Yeah, she's a full-time resident at the galleria.

168
00:09:30,729 --> 00:09:33,229
I think she hit every store in the mall.

169
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,887
Except for unicornucopia.

170
00:09:36,464 --> 00:09:37,198
Hmm.

171
00:09:38,090 --> 00:09:39,664
Any idea what this is?

172
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:41,083
No.

173
00:09:42,037 --> 00:09:44,840
So, if you were gonna help me, where would you start?

174
00:09:44,891 --> 00:09:46,155
With the obvious.

175
00:09:46,423 --> 00:09:49,917
I'd figure out if cora had any of the things on the list.

176
00:09:56,189 --> 00:09:58,249
I'm here to pick up my papers.

177
00:09:58,781 --> 00:10:03,101
I'm talking about the personal documents that you stole from my house.

178
00:10:03,152 --> 00:10:04,678
I didn't steal, Alicia.

179
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:08,687
Borrowed without my knowledge, accidentally dropped into your briefcase --

180
00:10:08,807 --> 00:10:10,759
I don't care what you're calling it.

181
00:10:10,810 --> 00:10:12,384
I just want them back.

182
00:10:19,632 --> 00:10:22,907
Why didn't you just tell me your ex-husband was a cop?

183
00:10:22,958 --> 00:10:25,010
I was trying to protect my son.

184
00:10:26,153 --> 00:10:30,590
I was young and scared, and Nathan woods was scary, violent, and high.

185
00:10:30,641 --> 00:10:33,699
I don't doubt that what you did was for the best.

186
00:10:33,801 --> 00:10:37,519
I'm just suggesting it might have been wise to let Wallace know.

187
00:10:37,570 --> 00:10:40,522
You are giving me parenting advice?

188
00:10:40,573 --> 00:10:41,821
What is that supposed to mean?

189
00:10:41,872 --> 00:10:45,694
That means I protected Wallace's childhood.
I didn't sell it out.

190
00:10:46,317 --> 00:10:48,758
I will not invite chaos into my house.

191
00:10:48,848 --> 00:10:51,647
Oh, come on, Alicia, you invited chaos!

192
00:10:51,698 --> 00:10:53,713
All you did was postpone it!

193
00:11:17,221 --> 00:11:21,030
Folks say papa never was much on thinkin'

194
00:11:21,401 --> 00:11:25,333
spent most of his time chasin' women and drinkin'

195
00:11:25,511 --> 00:11:28,113
mama, I'm dependin' on you

196
00:11:28,226 --> 00:11:30,629
to tell me the truth

197
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:33,992
mama looked up with a tear in her eye and said, "son..."

198
00:11:34,043 --> 00:11:41,266
papa was a rolling stone wherever he laid his hat was his home

199
00:11:41,502 --> 00:11:47,317
and when he died all he left us was alone

200
00:11:47,368 --> 00:11:49,630
talked with your moms about me, huh?

201
00:11:49,926 --> 00:11:53,124
Don't worry. I'm not here to defend myself.

202
00:11:57,060 --> 00:11:59,702
Truth is, I barely remember those days.

203
00:11:59,938 --> 00:12:02,232
So how can I blame her for running out on me?

204
00:12:02,283 --> 00:12:03,773
So why are you here?

205
00:12:04,732 --> 00:12:06,558
What brought you to Neptune?

206
00:12:07,522 --> 00:12:10,004
You had almost 18 years to track me down.

207
00:12:10,055 --> 00:12:11,453
She never told you?

208
00:12:11,621 --> 00:12:12,443
Told me what?

209
00:12:12,494 --> 00:12:13,548
I did try --

210
00:12:13,761 --> 00:12:15,121
for years, Wallace.

211
00:12:16,036 --> 00:12:19,564
It drove me crazy to think my son would grow up a stranger.

212
00:12:19,628 --> 00:12:22,552
Alicia's mom wouldn't tell me where she'd gone.

213
00:12:25,428 --> 00:12:28,016
She did promise to pass along these.

214
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:32,816
Grandma always liked me, I guess.

215
00:12:34,221 --> 00:12:38,177
If it weren't for her, I never would have known Alicia was pregnant.

216
00:12:40,344 --> 00:12:42,123
Mom said she gave you a choice.

217
00:12:42,174 --> 00:12:44,612
She said, "your job or being a father."

218
00:12:46,283 --> 00:12:50,141
If she would have given me that choice, I would have chose you.

219
00:12:52,144 --> 00:12:55,336
The votes have been tallied, and the nominees for king are...

220
00:12:55,387 --> 00:12:56,475
Duncan Kane...

221
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:58,218
Mark Fraser...

222
00:12:58,962 --> 00:13:00,208
Steve Vargo...

223
