00:14:33,693 --> 00:14:35,872
Okay, outlet mall outside of chatsworth.

259
00:14:35,923 --> 00:14:37,541
I'm going later to get my homecoming dress.

260
00:14:37,592 --> 00:14:38,463
Can I come?

261
00:14:38,514 --> 00:14:41,160
We can carpool, save a little money on gas.

262
00:14:41,211 --> 00:14:42,265
That's cool.

263
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:43,855
I'll call you.

264
00:14:47,338 --> 00:14:50,900
Though I haven't really been asked to homecoming yet, have I?

265
00:14:57,852 --> 00:14:59,334
So, I was thinking --

266
00:14:59,779 --> 00:15:02,660
you're an emancipated minor, I'm an emancipated minor.

267
00:15:02,711 --> 00:15:04,307
Maybe we should get together thursday night,

268
00:15:04,358 --> 00:15:06,484
chug cough syrup, mug some old ladies?

269
00:15:06,535 --> 00:15:08,184
Oh, golly, I don't know.

270
00:15:08,235 --> 00:15:13,099
I was thinking about staying home, making a hope quilt for the lonely.

271
00:15:13,384 --> 00:15:14,866
A little "hot shots"?

272
00:15:15,156 --> 00:15:16,202
Golf tourney?

273
00:15:16,424 --> 00:15:17,948
A little room service?

274
00:15:18,973 --> 00:15:20,137
You're on.

275
00:15:25,302 --> 00:15:27,706
So, she's got to be the thief, right?

276
00:15:28,183 --> 00:15:28,927
Well...

277
00:15:29,692 --> 00:15:32,110
let me just double-check before you accuse her of anything.

278
00:15:32,161 --> 00:15:36,449
But she'd have to be pretty thick to wear stolen merchandise to school.

279
00:15:36,623 --> 00:15:40,369
The girl's sweet, but she's not the brightest bulb on the bush.

280
00:15:40,486 --> 00:15:43,654
I should have a definitive answer for you by tomorrow.

281
00:15:45,660 --> 00:15:46,697
You know what else bugs me?

282
00:15:46,748 --> 00:15:48,250
Gang violence bugs me.

283
00:15:48,301 --> 00:15:49,620
Illegal immigration bugs me.

284
00:15:49,671 --> 00:15:51,349
Drug trafficking bugs me.

285
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:53,277
Street-racing bugs me.

286
00:15:53,328 --> 00:15:54,129
But come election day,

287
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:57,462
I am confident that the voters of balboa county will do what is best and put

288
00:15:57,513 --> 00:15:59,643
"the exterminator" back in office.

289
00:16:02,518 --> 00:16:04,465
Next question to you, Mr. Mars.

290
00:16:04,516 --> 00:16:07,799
We're all familiar with your role in the Lilly Kane murder case.

291
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:11,754
Does the nature of that crime or the conditions of your recall

292
00:16:11,926 --> 00:16:13,920
color your feelings for Neptune?

293
00:16:14,344 --> 00:16:15,484
I love Neptune.

294
00:16:15,535 --> 00:16:17,527
I wouldn't be running if I didn't.

295
00:16:17,578 --> 00:16:18,356
But...

296
00:16:19,325 --> 00:16:22,109
what does -- to borrow a slogan -- "bug me"

297
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:25,868
are the subtle changes in Neptune over the last few months.

298
00:16:25,919 --> 00:16:28,131
You mean violent crime dropping 11%?

299
00:16:28,188 --> 00:16:31,138
I'm talking about the growing sense of resentment,

300
00:16:31,629 --> 00:16:34,890
of friction, of polarization within our community.

301
00:16:39,424 --> 00:16:42,318
Well, nothing has been more divisive than the bus crash,

302
00:16:42,369 --> 00:16:47,416
and many feel that you were quick in attributing the accident to driver error, sheriff.

303
00:16:47,671 --> 00:16:53,654
On the subject of the bus crash, it's just come to light that back in '89, then--

304
00:16:54,003 --> 00:16:58,384
deputy Mars pulled ed Doyle over for driving under the influence.

305
00:16:58,435 --> 00:17:02,375
He had simply decided to follow him home rather than follow procedure.

306
00:17:02,511 --> 00:17:04,173
Had a D.U.I. Appeared on his record,

307
00:17:04,224 --> 00:17:07,392
he would have never been hired by the school district.

308
00:17:09,601 --> 00:17:11,521
Mr. Mars, your response.

309
00:17:11,773 --> 00:17:13,616
I'm sorry. I'm n--
I'm not familiar with it.

310
00:17:13,667 --> 00:17:18,201
It's okay -- I have a copy of your patrol log if you need to jog your memory.

311
00:17:24,205 --> 00:17:27,094
This, I have the only car left in america without a cupholder,

312
00:17:27,145 --> 00:17:31,277
so now I end up with a caramel Latte rorschach test all over my blouse.

313
00:17:31,565 --> 00:17:35,195
- Thanks for letting me borrow something of yours.
- No problem.

314
00:17:35,870 --> 00:17:38,655
Must find stolen goods.

315
00:17:39,085 --> 00:17:40,830
You know, the mall's in chatsworth.

316
00:17:40,881 --> 00:17:43,277
No one worth knowing is gonna see you.

317
00:17:44,871 --> 00:17:45,306
Oh.

318
00:17:45,306 --> 00:17:46,159
No, not that one.

319
00:17:46,210 --> 00:17:47,853
There's nothing you'd want to see in there.

320
00:17:47,904 --> 00:17:49,706
I love looking through your clothes.

321
00:17:49,757 --> 00:17:52,892
It's like the fashion equivalent of a skin mag.

322
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,900
No, seriously, I don't --

323
00:17:57,434 --> 00:17:58,172
oh...

324
00:17:58,874 --> 00:17:59,660
yeah.

325
00:18:00,597 --> 00:18:02,875
I so did not want you to see that.

326
00:18:03,629 --> 00:18:04,289
Isn't this...

327
00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:07,262
the oh, boyo pollo chicken.

328
00:18:07,765 --> 00:18:08,388
Yep.

329
00:18:09,036 --> 00:18:13,436
You know, if anyone finds out about this, I'm afraid I'll have to kill you.

330
00:18:14,008 --> 00:18:16,477
If I tell anyone, I won't blame you.

331
00:18:26,372 --> 00:18:27,558
Your dress is perfect.

332
00:18:27,609 --> 00:18:29,225
Duncan's gonna love it.

333
00:18:29,615 --> 00:18:30,359
Thanks.

334
00:18:31,648 --> 00:18:34,992
Outlet therapy is considerably better than retail therapy.

335
00:18:36,502 --> 00:18:37,850
Thanks for driving.

336
00:18:38,105 --> 00:18:38,723
Bye.

337
00:18:49,081 --> 00:18:50,311
Oh, boyo pollo?

338
00:18:50,405 --> 00:18:52,709
May I speak with the manager, please?

339
00:18:52,809 --> 00:18:54,718
Hi, this is may hadwell.

340
00:18:54,769 --> 00:18:57,717
I'm the vocational ed coordinator at Neptune high.

341
00:18:57,768 --> 00:19:01,067
I need to verify some work hours for cora briggs.

342
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:06,304
She worked sunday, as well?

343
00:19:07,087 --> 00:19:08,309
Until what time?

344
00:19:10,612 --> 00:19:11,926
I see. Thank you.

345
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,409
Jackie, it's Veronica.

346
00:19:20,892 --> 00:19:23,808
There's no way cora could have stolen your card.

347
00:19:24,196 --> 00:19:25,946
We're back to square one.

348
00:19:27,801 --> 00:19:28,757
Thanks, Carl.

349
00:19:28,808 --> 00:19:29,602
Mm-hmm.

350
00:19:32,897 --> 00:19:34,907
It's weird that you live here.

351
00:19:35,254 --> 00:19:38,136
I don't want you going all howard hughes-y on me.

352
00:19:38,187 --> 00:19:39,685
I am not a shut-in.

353
00:19:39,838 --> 00:19:40,753
These nails --

354
00:19:40,804 --> 00:19:41,934
neatly trimmed.

355
00:19:42,381 --> 00:19:45,439
Though, now that you mention it, I have started bottling my own urine.

356
00:19:45,490 --> 00:19:46,090
Ew.

357
00:19:50,510 --> 00:19:51,128
Hey!

358
00:19:51,186 --> 00:19:55,100
What do you say we invite some people over here for an after party?

359
00:19:55,169 --> 00:19:56,704
After party?

360
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:58,145
After what?

361
00:20:00,705 --> 00:20:01,780
The homecoming dance?

362
00:20:01,831 --> 00:20:03,739
The thing after the big game?

363
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:04,668
Oh...

364
00:20:05,283 --> 00:20:08,191
tell me more of this thing you call "homecoming."

365
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,400
I haven't asked you yet.

366
00:20:11,451 --> 00:20:12,373
Mnh-mnh.

367
00:20:12,456 --> 00:20:13,778
I'm such a dope.

368
00:20:15,229 --> 00:20:17,754
Well, of course I want you to go with me.

369
00:20:17,805 --> 00:20:19,143
You're my woman.

370
00:20:19,345 --> 00:20:21,215
See?
Was that so hard?

371
00:20:21,557 --> 00:20:22,217
Okay.

372
00:20:22,723 --> 00:20:25,029
I'll be needing an orchid wristlet --

373
00:20:25,312 --> 00:20:27,515
preferably in the fuchsia family --

374
00:20:27,569 --> 00:20:32,772
a rolls-royce limo, and some Kane software stationery.

375
00:20:34,837 --> 00:20:36,830
Seriously? Stationery?

376
00:20:37,415 --> 00:20:38,511
What for?

377
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:40,985
You're here for your looks.

378
00:20:41,036 --> 00:20:44,136
Why don't you leave the heavy thinking to me, sugarpants?

379
00:20:44,187 --> 00:20:46,013
Now go make yourself pretty.

380
00:20:51,895 --> 00:20:53,859
"After surrendering an early lead,

381
00:20:53,910 --> 00:20:58,585
"former sheriff keith Mars is now in a statistical dead heat with the incumbent."

382
00:20:59,147 --> 00:21:02,063
What do your number guys have to say about that?

383
00:21:06,018 --> 00:21:07,008
Criminy.

384
00:21:07,653 --> 00:21:09,403
What kind of bug is that?

385
00:21:10,255 --> 00:21:11,588
You worry about the election.

386
00:21:11,639 --> 00:21:13,778
I'll worry about my bio project.

387
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:22,130
What are those?

388
00:21:22,264 --> 00:21:23,494
Don't you know?

389
00:21:24,045 --> 00:21:26,693
It looks an awful lot like your handwriting.

390
00:21:27,621 --> 00:21:30,076
"Return to sender." Hmm.

391
00:21:30,959 --> 00:21:32,849
Maybe we should just see what dad has to say.

392
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,538
It's better late than never, right?

393
00:21:34,589 --> 00:21:35,566
No, Wallace, no!

394
00:21:35,617 --> 00:21:37,009
What were you thinking, mom?

395
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:40,856
That he was so strung out, he'd O.D.
And just forget about me?

396
00:21:40,959 --> 00:21:44,078
I'm still your mother, and I told you to stay away from him,

397
00:21:44,129 --> 00:21:45,425
and I expect you to listen to me!

398
00:21:45,476 --> 00:21:47,704
You told me you gave him a choice.

399
00:21:48,023 --> 00:21:48,901
You lied.

400
00:21:56,070 --> 00:22:00,554
She made my dad out to be some kind of a psychopath just to cover her tracks.

401
00:22:00,730 --> 00:22:04,354
If he's so nuts, how'd he manage to stick with the Chicago P.D. all these years?

402
00:22:04,405 --> 00:22:08,600
If he was a cop, how did it take him all these years to track you down?

403
00:22:08,651 --> 00:22:10,055
Your mom is right, Wallace.

404
00:22:10,106 --> 00:22:12,318
He had his chance, and he passed it up.

405
00:22:12,369 --> 00:22:14,371
Take it from someone who knows.

406
00:22:14,529 --> 00:22:17,537
The one who sticks with you is the one who cares.

407
00:22:32,650 --> 00:22:33,793
Sorry to interrupt.

408
00:22:33,844 --> 00:22:35,024
Check this out.

409
00:22:35,453 --> 00:22:38,636
Jake Kane sent a vote of support all the way from aspen.

410
00:22:38,687 --> 00:22:41,654
"Dear exterminator, knock 'em dead on election day."

411
00:22:41,705 --> 00:22:43,605
Got those guys in interrogation.

412
00:22:43,656 --> 00:22:46,178
The two goons you picked up in cliffside?

413
00:22:46,346 --> 00:22:49,782
You're not gonna believe the story they're trying to sell.

414
00:23:00,623 --> 00:23:05,099
Consolidated elemental industries, 5003 james --

415
00:23:05,163 --> 00:23:08,071
the first place where someone used Jackie's card.

416
00:23:12,739 --> 00:23:16,701
Yeah, when I think of elemental industries, I think of palm readings.

417
00:23:21,145 --> 00:23:22,903
I'll be out in a minute.

418
00:23:33,951 --> 00:23:35,701
Vanilla-scented candles...

419
00:23:35,873 --> 00:23:38,057
$500 worth, perhaps?

420
00:23:38,235 --> 00:23:39,365
Purchased at...

421
00:23:41,056 --> 00:23:42,228
...tricky wicks.

422
00:23:47,226 --> 00:23:49,211
It just doesn't make much sense.

423
00:23:49,262 --> 00:23:51,524
How would she have gotten your card?

424
00:23:52,205 --> 00:23:56,896
Although I guess it's possible that cora and the psychic were in this together.

425
00:23:57,707 --> 00:23:59,976
I know how madam sophie got the card.

426
00:24:00,027 --> 00:24:01,475
She got it from me.

427
00:24:02,909 --> 00:24:03,913
You see a psychic?

428
00:24:03,964 --> 00:24:05,919
My grandma died two years ago,

429
00:24:05,970 --> 00:24:09,464
and even a person pretending to be grandma

430
00:24:09,515 --> 00:24:12,985
telling me everything's gonna be all right gives me comfort.

431
00:24:13,246 --> 00:24:13,864
Shh.

432
00:24:13,932 --> 00:24:15,464
It's my secret shame.

433
00:24:17,135 --> 00:24:18,893
I'm sure you've got one.

434
00:24:21,203 --> 00:24:22,551
Remember mamma-max?

435
00:24:23,937 --> 00:24:27,724
The stuff from the infomercial, the cream that you rub on your chest?

436
00:24:27,775 --> 00:24:28,569
Mm-hmm.

437
00:24:29,071 --> 00:24:31,618
In my defense, I was a freshman.

438
00:24:32,706 --> 00:24:33,810
I've got it.

439
00:24:34,875 --> 00:24:36,683
I know how to get even.

440
00:24:36,799 --> 00:24:38,327
I'm going on her show.

441
00:24:38,378 --> 00:24:39,608
She has a show?

442
00:24:40,081 --> 00:24:42,414
You tivo a community access show?

443
00:24:42,617 --> 00:24:44,829
Everyone at Neptune high watches it.

444
00:24:47,802 --> 00:24:49,233
Welcome, everyone.

445
00:24:49,726 --> 00:24:52,243
Someone special is trying to reach you...

446
00:24:52,668 --> 00:24:56,310
a friend who passed before her time.

447
00:24:58,822 --> 00:25:00,832
Do you know who that might be?

448
00:25:00,890 --> 00:25:02,036
I think I do.

449
00:25:03,736 --> 00:25:05,084
My friend rhonda...

450
00:25:06,415 --> 00:25:07,902
she was on the bus.

451
00:25:13,152 --> 00:25:16,152
And suddenly I have a new life's mission --

452
00:25:16,203 --> 00:25:17,837
destroy madam sophie.

453
00:25:21,045 --> 00:25:23,039
Dad, you remember Veronica Mars.

454
00:25:23,142 --> 00:25:24,534
We met at shark field.

455
00:25:24,585 --> 00:25:27,220
Right -- promised you wouldn't wash that hand.

456
00:25:27,271 --> 00:25:28,264
I haven'T.

457
00:25:28,994 --> 00:25:30,988
People are starting to complain.

458
00:25:31,433 --> 00:25:33,175
What did the sheriff want?

459
00:25:33,416 --> 00:25:35,961
He wanted me to emcee the department's charity ball.

460
00:25:36,012 --> 00:25:37,192
You're kidding.

461
00:25:37,459 --> 00:25:38,471
Wish I was.

462
00:25:39,676 --> 00:25:41,292
It was nice seeing you.

463
00:25:42,230 --> 00:25:43,306
Before I left her place,

464
00:25:43,357 --> 00:25:46,660
Jackie and I came up with a plan to get even with madam sophie.

465
00:25:46,711 --> 00:25:48,218
Since she already knew Jackie,

466
00:25:48,269 --> 00:25:51,889
I would go on madam sophie's show and expose her as a fraud.

467
00:25:52,253 --> 00:25:55,808
Terrence Cook's mention of his visit with the sheriff reminded me --

468
00:25:55,859 --> 00:26:00,291
maybe it's time to check in on Neptune's finest dirty politician himself.

469
00:26:02,265 --> 00:26:05,231
You have to make a report on your own, sweetheart.

470
00:26:05,282 --> 00:26:06,202
Thank you.

471
00:26:14,414 --> 00:26:15,292
Mr. Cook.

472
00:26:15,622 --> 00:26:17,238
Good to see you,heriff.

473
00:26:22,807 --> 00:26:27,133
I was thinking that you might be interested in buying some tickets to our annual fundraiser.

474
00:26:27,184 --> 00:26:28,731
They're 10 bucks a pop.

475
00:26:28,782 --> 00:26:31,691
You asked me to come all the way down here just to hit me up for a donation?

476
00:26:31,742 --> 00:26:34,784
I like to get to know our more notable residents --

477
00:26:35,127 --> 00:26:38,236
business leaders, hollywood types, all-star athletes --

478
00:26:38,287 --> 00:26:39,199
personally.

479
00:26:39,963 --> 00:26:41,453
Put me down for two.

480
00:26:41,607 --> 00:26:43,575
It was real nice to meet you.

481
00:26:44,219 --> 00:26:48,075
Actually, I was thinking you might purchase more like 1,000 tickets.

482
00:26:48,939 --> 00:26:53,438
Oh, and if you could emcee the bachelor auction, that would be great.

483
00:26:53,750 --> 00:26:55,291
That's a lot of money, sheriff.

484
00:26:55,342 --> 00:26:57,245
Yeah, that's $10,000...

485
00:26:57,779 --> 00:26:59,311
if my math's correct.

486
00:27:00,071 --> 00:27:02,319
Hey, it's not $3 million.

487
00:27:02,388 --> 00:27:04,807
Now, that is real money.

488
00:27:04,912 --> 00:27:11,165
I mean, that's the kind of money that certain people take very, very seriously.

489
00:27:12,106 --> 00:27:13,188
Gambling debt like that,

490
00:27:13,239 --> 00:27:20,001
and they might send some guys down to your nice new cliffside house to remind you payment's due.

491
00:27:20,203 --> 00:27:21,320
What are you getting at, sheriff?

492
00:27:21,371 --> 00:27:23,500
Pretty sure I just got to it, slugger.

493
00:27:23,551 --> 00:27:25,400
I never bet on baseball.

494
00:27:28,538 --> 00:27:31,160
I got a guy in a holding cell back there.

495
00:27:32,628 --> 00:27:36,407
Says you did favors for gentlemen who bet extensively...

496
00:27:36,947 --> 00:27:38,013
on baseball.

497
00:27:42,387 --> 00:27:43,005
Hmm.

498
00:27:45,989 --> 00:27:48,075
We both have something in common.

499
00:27:48,420 --> 00:27:51,872
We'd both like to see you make it into the hall of fame.

500
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:58,550
Say it ain't so, terrence.

501
00:28:00,672 --> 00:28:02,514
Do you mind if I sit here?

502
00:28:03,331 --> 00:28:04,461
Michele, right?

503
00:28:05,052 --> 00:28:06,572
I saw you on tv --

504
00:28:06,721 --> 00:28:10,109
"answers from angels." That was pretty amazing.

505
00:28:10,160 --> 00:28:11,348
Oh, it so was.

506
00:28:12,251 --> 00:28:13,823
The reason I wanted to talk --

507
00:28:13,874 --> 00:28:16,614
I'm thinking about going on the show, and...

508
00:28:17,335 --> 00:28:19,922
what exactly did they have you do when you got there?

509
00:28:19,973 --> 00:28:24,245
Did someone from the show ask you who you wanted to communicate with?

510
00:28:24,475 --> 00:28:25,220
Oh.

511
00:28:26,253 --> 00:28:28,528
No. No, not at all.

512
00:28:28,579 --> 00:28:30,520
So nobody there knew about rhonda?

513
00:28:30,571 --> 00:28:33,130
Well, there was this one lady backstage,

514
00:28:33,181 --> 00:28:36,131
this other audience member, and we got to talking.

515
00:28:36,383 --> 00:28:37,454
What did she look like?

516
00:28:37,505 --> 00:28:38,207
Crazy.

517
00:28:39,185 --> 00:28:40,385
Big hair...

518
00:28:40,943 --> 00:28:42,241
rhinestone glasses.

519
00:28:42,957 --> 00:28:43,575
Why?

